  "prompt": "What are the major events that happened in 1997?",
  "response": "1997 was a pretty eventful year! Here's a breakdown of some of the major events:\n\n**Politics & International Relations:**\n\n*   **Hong Kong Handover:**  A huge moment!  On July 1st, Hong Kong was transferred from British to Chinese control, ending over 150 years of British rule.\n*   **Death of Princess Diana:**  The death of Princess Diana in a car crash in Paris on August 31st shocked the world and led to an outpouring of grief.\n*   **Kyoto Protocol:**  This landmark international agreement to combat climate change was adopted in Kyoto, Japan, in December.  It committed industrialized nations to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.\n*   **Asian Financial Crisis Begins:**  The Thai baht collapsed in July, triggering a financial crisis that spread rapidly throughout Southeast Asia and beyond.\n*   **Madeleine Albright becomes first female US Secretary of State:** She was sworn in on January 23rd, breaking a major barrier in American politics.\n\n**Technology & Culture:**\n\n*   **Deep Blue beats Garry Kasparov:**  In May, the IBM supercomputer Deep Blue defeated world chess champion Garry Kasparov in a six-game match, a significant milestone in artificial intelligence.\n*   **Harry Potter Takes Off:**  *Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone* (released as *Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone* in the US) was published, launching the global phenomenon.\n*   **Titanic Movie:**  The epic film *Titanic* was released in December and became a massive box office hit, winning numerous awards.\n*   **Launch of DVD Players:** DVD players started to become available to consumers, marking a shift from VHS tapes.\n\n**Other Notable Events:**\n\n*   **Hale-Bopp Comet:** The Hale-Bopp comet made its closest approach to Earth, providing a spectacular sight in the night sky for much of the year.\n*   **Heaven's Gate Mass Suicide:**  The Heaven's Gate cult committed mass suicide in Rancho Santa Fe, California, believing they would ascend to a spaceship following the Hale-Bopp comet.\n\nThis is not an exhaustive list, but covers many of the most significant and widely remembered events of 1997.\n",
